						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab near the temple of Kalamēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This inscription referring itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> is dated in <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year (lost), Āshāḍha, Sunday, lunar eclipse.</hi> It refers to <hi rend="bold">Jākalamahādēvi the queen of Vikramāditya,</hi> as governing a territory the name of which is lost. The record is very badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
